        public SidebarSavedState(android.os.Parcelable superState)

      • SidebarSavedState

        public SidebarSavedState(android.os.Parcel source)
        Creates a new data structure, which allows to store the internal state of a Sidebar. This constructor is used when reading from a parcel. It reads the state of the superclass.
        Parameters:
        source - The parcel to read read from as a instance of the class Parcel. The parcel may not be null
